<br>
I'm a warrior in a small group of 6 currently in our early 50s.  I already use Lamentation in my primary, and the Katana of Endurence ( 18/30  +10 AC +10 Dex  +10 Sta  +20 HPs  +10 Disease and Poison)<br>
<br>
We recently found a second Lamentation, and I'm wondering if the lower delay would be worth my while for holding aggro.  Or is Lamentation just no good for an off-hander compared to the ratio and stats of the Katana?  As it is, with either sword, everyone in the group can steal aggro from me anytime they want.<br>
<br>
I certainly attack a lot faster, and with all the numbers running across the screen, it almost seems as if I'm doing more damage, although that's probably not the case.<br>
<br>
We will probably be doing things like Hate, Juggs, Cazic Thule and the like soon, and any help would be appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxiththewizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xith the Wizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/02 2:26:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4147.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Secondary weapon</span><hr size=1> if you can afford it ... buy frostbringer ... <br>
<br>
will be the best investment you ever make. <br>
<br>
No use in haveing all those stats floating around, if you cant hold aggro.  Tanks without aggro are no more use than a cleric without mana.<br>
<br>
Use Lammy mainhand, frosty offhand, you will have much much less problems with maintaining aggro.<br>
<br>
Keep the katana around for times when you need to be in a damage role, then mainhand frosty, offhand katana (for the superior ratio).  Untill you get something better that is. <p>Master Xith N'Shezbenon
